uch as by Adrienne Rich, bell hooks, Donna Haraway and Judith Butler) that are acknowledged by renowned authors for their significance concerning media research based on sound social concepts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aFeminist theory. 0aFeministische Theorie. 0aGender. 0aGeschlecht. 0aHerrschaft. 0aKritische Medienforschung. 0aMacht. 0aMass mediaxResearch. 0aMedia Aesthetics. 0aMedia Culture. 0aMedia Studies. 0aMedia Theory. 0aMedia. 0aMedien. 0aMedienästhetik. 0aMedienkultur. 0aMedientheorie. 0aMedienwissenschaft. 0aPower Relations. 0aPower. 0aRepräsentation. 0aRepresentative government and representation. 4aFeministische Theorie. 4aGender Studies. 4aGender. 4aGeschlecht. 4aHerrschaft. 4aKritische Medienforschung. 4aMacht. 4aMedien. 4aMedienkultur. 4aMedientheorie. 4aMedienwissenschaft. 4aMedienästhetik. 4aRepräsentation. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aCritical Media Studies.  aFeminist Theory.  aGender Studies.  aGender.  aMedia Aesthetics.  aMedia Culture.  aMedia Studies.  aMedia Theory.  aMedia.  aPower Relations.  aPower.  aRepresentation.1 aAnzaldúa, Gloria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarry, Kathy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBordo, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraidotti, Rosi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurris, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButler, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChen, Nancy N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrenshaw, Kimberlé W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relato